00032 #ifndef CONSTRAINT_POW_H
00033 #define CONSTRAINT_POW_H

00035 #include <math.h>

00037 // This constraint is half-way to being changed from using
00038 // LRINT to roundup and rounddown. Still don't quite have my head around
00039 // this +0.5 business. Or at least I'm not convinced that it's OK.
00040 // at least now it passes test_nightingale_pow.minion.
00041 
00042 #ifndef LRINT
00043 #define LRINT(x) static_cast<DomainInt>(x + 0.5)
00044 #endif
00045 
00047 template<typename VarRef1, typename VarRef2, typename VarRef3>
00048 struct PowConstraint : public AbstractConstraint
00049 {
00050   virtual string constraint_name()
00051   { return "Pow"; }
00052   
00053   VarRef1 var1;
00054   VarRef2 var2;
00055   VarRef3 var3;
00056   
00057   PowConstraint(StateObj* _stateObj, VarRef1 _var1, VarRef2 _var2, VarRef3 _var3) :
00058     AbstractConstraint(_stateObj), var1(_var1), var2(_var2), var3(_var3)
00059   {
00060   
00061       if(var1.getInitialMin() < 0 || var2.getInitialMin() < 0 ||
00062          var3.getInitialMin() < 0)
00063       { 
00064           FAIL_EXIT("The 'pow' constraint only supports non-negative numbers at present.");
00065       }
00066       if(var2.getInitialMin()==0)
00067       {
00068           FAIL_EXIT("The 'pow' constraint (x^y = z) does not allow y to contain 0, to avoid the case 0^0.");
00069       }
00070   }
00071   
00072   virtual triggerCollection setup_internal()
00073   {
00074     triggerCollection t;
00075     t.push_back(make_trigger(var1, Trigger(this, -1), LowerBound));
00076     t.push_back(make_trigger(var2, Trigger(this, -2), LowerBound));
00077     t.push_back(make_trigger(var3, Trigger(this, -3), LowerBound));
00078     t.push_back(make_trigger(var1, Trigger(this, 1), UpperBound));
00079     t.push_back(make_trigger(var2, Trigger(this, 2), UpperBound));
00080     t.push_back(make_trigger(var3, Trigger(this, 3), UpperBound));
00081     return t;
00082   }
00083   
00084   inline DomainInt roundup(double x)
00085   {
00086     // remember all numbers are non-negative in here, so
00087     // how are we going to hit the lower limit for ints?
00088     if(x<std::numeric_limits<DomainInt>::min())
00089     {
00090       return std::numeric_limits<DomainInt>::min();
00091     }
00092     else
00093     {
00094       return static_cast<DomainInt>(x);  // Actually this should round up!
00095     }
00096 }
00097     
00098   inline DomainInt rounddown(double x)
00099   {
00100     if(x>std::numeric_limits<DomainInt>::max())
00101     {
00102       return std::numeric_limits<DomainInt>::max();
00103     }
00104     else
00105     {
00106       return static_cast<DomainInt>(x);  
00107     }
00108   }
00109   
00110   
00111   double my_pow(DomainInt x, DomainInt y)
00112   { return pow(checked_cast<double>(x), checked_cast<double>(y));}
00113   
00114   double my_y(DomainInt x, DomainInt z)
00115   { return log(checked_cast<double>(z)) / log(checked_cast<double>(x)); }
00116   
00117   double my_x(DomainInt y, DomainInt z)
00118   { return exp(log(checked_cast<double>(z)) / checked_cast<double>(y)); }
00119   
00120   virtual void propagate(int flag, DomainDelta)
00121   {
00122     PROP_INFO_ADDONE(Pow);
00123     switch(flag)
00124     {
00125       case -1:
00126       {
00127         // var3 >= min(var1) ^ min(var2)
00128         var3.setMin(LRINT(my_pow(var1.getMin(),var2.getMin())));
00129         DomainInt var1_min = var1.getMin();
00130         if(var1_min > 1)
00131           // var2 <= log base max(var3) of min(var1)
00132           var2.setMax(LRINT(my_y(var1_min, var3.getMax())));
00133         break;
00134       }
00135       case -2:
00136         // var3>= min(var1) ^ min(var2) 
00137         var3.setMin(LRINT(my_pow(var1.getMin(), var2.getMin())));
00138         var1.setMax(LRINT(my_x(var2.getMin(), var3.getMax())));
00139         break;
00140         
00141       case -3:
00142       {
00143         var1.setMin(LRINT(my_x(var2.getMax(), var3.getMin())));
00144         DomainInt var1_max = var1.getMax();
00145         if(var1_max > 1)
00146           var2.setMin(LRINT(my_y(var1_max, var3.getMin())));
00147         break;
00148       }
00149       case 1:
00150       {
00151         var3.setMax(rounddown(my_pow(var1.getMax(),var2.getMax())));  // wraparound was occurring here, so use rounddown
00152         DomainInt var1_max = var1.getMax();
00153         if(var1_max > 1)
00154           var2.setMin(LRINT(my_y(var1_max, var3.getMin())));
00155         break;
00156       }
00157       case 2:
00158         var3.setMax(rounddown(my_pow(var1.getMax(), var2.getMax())));  // wraparound here.
00159         var1.setMin(LRINT(my_x(var2.getMax(), var3.getMin())));
00160         break;
00161         
00162       case 3:
00163       {
00164         var1.setMax(LRINT(my_x(var2.getMin(), var3.getMax())));
00165         DomainInt var1_min = var1.getMin();
00166         if(var1_min > 1)
00167           var2.setMax(LRINT(my_y(var1_min, var3.getMax())));
00168         break;
00169       }
00170     }
00171   }
00172   
00173   virtual void full_propagate()
00174   { 
00175     propagate(1,0); 
00176     propagate(2,0);
00177     propagate(3,0);
00178     propagate(-1,0);
00179     propagate(-2,0);
00180     propagate(-3,0);
00181   }
00182   
00183   virtual BOOL check_assignment(DomainInt* v, int v_size)
00184   {
00185     D_ASSERT(v_size == 3);
00186     return my_pow(v[0],v[1]) == v[2];
00187   }
00188   
00189   virtual vector<AnyVarRef> get_vars()
00190   { 
00191     vector<AnyVarRef> v;
00192     v.push_back(var1);
00193     v.push_back(var2);
00194     v.push_back(var3);
00195     return v;
00196   }
00197   
00198   virtual bool get_satisfying_assignment(box<pair<int,DomainInt> >& assignment)
00199    {  
00200      for(DomainInt v1 = var1.getMin(); v1 <= var1.getMax(); ++v1)
00201      {
00202        if(var1.inDomain(v1))
00203        {
00204          for(DomainInt v2 = var2.getMin(); v2 <= var2.getMax(); ++v2)
00205          {
00206            if(var2.inDomain(v2) && var3.inDomain(my_pow(v1, v2)))  // implicit conversion here causes a warning -- perh use roundup or rounddown
00207            {
00208              assignment.push_back(make_pair(0, v1));
00209              assignment.push_back(make_pair(1, v2));
00210              assignment.push_back(make_pair(2, my_pow(v1, v2)));
00211              return true;
00212            }
00213          }
00214        }
00215      }
00216      return false;
00217    }
00218     
00219      // Function to make it reifiable in the lousiest way.
00220   virtual AbstractConstraint* reverse_constraint()
00221   {
00222       vector<AnyVarRef> t;
00223       t.push_back(var1);
00224       t.push_back(var2);
00225       t.push_back(var3);
00226       return new CheckAssignConstraint<vector<AnyVarRef>, PowConstraint>(stateObj, t, *this);
00227   }
00228 };

00230 template<typename V1, typename V2>
00231 inline AbstractConstraint*
00232 BuildCT_POW(StateObj* stateObj, const V1& vars, const V2& var2, ConstraintBlob&)
00233 {
00234   D_ASSERT(vars.size() == 2);
00235   D_ASSERT(var2.size() == 1);
00236   return new PowConstraint<typename V1::value_type, typename V1::value_type,
00237                            typename V2::value_type>(stateObj, vars[0], vars[1], var2[0]);
00238 }
